","id":"0","title":"BitBuckets FRC 4183 Wiki"},"1":{"body":"This is a site for storing all of the information and documentation required to quickly understand BitBuckets related concepts","breadcrumbs":"Introduction » What is this?","id":"1","title":"What is this?"},"10":{"body":"The Software subdivision of BitBuckets handles all of the code that controls the robot, as opposed to the structure and design of the robot","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » What do we do?","id":"10","title":"What do we do?"},"11":{"body":"Software revolves around writing subsystems, or compartmentalized blocks of code for each aspect that the robot needs to have. For instance, if the robot needs to move based on what it sees, we would have a Drive subsystem control the wheels and communicate with a Vision subsystem to tell it where to go. You'll be working with Java a lot so it's important to have a grasp on not just the basics but many specifics of the language like Object Oriented Design We'll also be working with a First Robotics specific library called WPILib which helps us control the robot parts' built in code","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » What will we learn/need to know?","id":"11","title":"What will we learn/need to know?"},"12":{"body":"Java (Code) Gradle (Dependency Manager) Git (Version Control) WPILib (Robot Library)","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » Tools we use","id":"12","title":"Tools we use"},"13":{"body":"Better than Mechanical Live in the Basement Write code and complain when it doesn't work Hackerman Interested? Head to Getting Started .","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » Highlights","id":"13","title":"Highlights"},"14":{"body":"This guide assumes you're on an apple device. If you are on windows, scroll down to the windows section","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » Getting Started » Getting Started","id":"14","title":"Getting Started"},"15":{"body":"Install intellij","breadcrumbs":"What is Software? » Getting Started » Set up Machine","id":"15","title":"Set 